    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="291"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d291">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">857H.01/104</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Latvia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="94" xml:id="d291fn94">Similar information was sent to the Department by
                        the Chargé in the Soviet Union in his despatch No. 1232, January 2, 1936;
                        received January 20.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1025</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-30">December 30,
                            1935</date>.<lb/>[Received January 14, 1936.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that the <hi
                        rend="italic">Collection of Laws and Orders of the U.S.S.R.</hi>, in its No.
                    17, Part II, of November 29, 1935, contains as item 138, the Treaty Concerning
                    the Archipelago of Spitsbergen, together with additions and an annex, signed at
                    Paris, February 9, 1920, with a note that the adhesion of the U.S.S.R. to this
                    Treaty was approved by the Central Executive Committee of the U.S.S.R. February
                    27, 1935, and came into effect May 7, 1935.</p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>J. V. A. <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
